Andrographis paniculata injection is a sterile, injectable preparation derived from the perennial herb Andrographis paniculata. The herb, native to tropical and subtropical regions of Asia, has a long history in Ayurvedic and Chinese medicine for its heat‑clearing, detoxifying, anti‑inflammatory and antibacterial properties. When formulated as an injectable, the extract delivers a rapid, standardized dose that supports the treatment of acute upper‑respiratory infections, bacterial pharyngitis, and a spectrum of inflammatory disorders. The convenience of a single‑dose vial, combined with the ability to integrate the product into existing hospital formularies, makes it an attractive adjunct to conventional antimicrobial and symptomatic therapies.

