Key Market Drivers
1. Rising Demand for Herbal Immunomodulators
Consumers worldwide are gravitating toward plant‑based immunomodulatory solutions, especially in regions that experience seasonal viral surges. Healthcare providers increasingly prescribe Andrographis injections to bolster innate immunity, support recovery from viral respiratory illnesses, and reduce reliance on broad‑spectrum antibiotics. Survey data from tertiary hospitals in China and India indicate a 12 % annual increase in injection volume over the past three years, reflecting strong clinician confidence.

2. Expanding Clinical Applications
Ongoing clinical trials are validating broader uses for the injection, including adjunct therapy for COVID‑19‑related cytokine storms, management of post‑operative inflammatory pain, and as a supportive treatment for allergic rhinitis. Early efficacy signals have prompted several biotech firms to explore combination regimens with conventional antivirals, potentially unlocking new revenue streams and expanding the addressable patient pool.

